{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, since e sA (k) converges to e sA in the strong operator topology as k → ∞, we know that along some subsequence e sA (k j) (X), we have convergence for almost every ω ∈ Ω, i.e.,",
    "which concludes the proof of (4.5).",
    "□ Lemma 4.14.",
    "The operator B ∈ L(E), B(X)(ω):= B(X(ω)), satisfies the weak B condition for A.",
    "We need to show that B is strictly positive, self-adjoint, A * B ∈ L(E) and -A * B + c 0 B ≥ 0 for some constant c 0 ≥ 0."
  ]
}